	<Title>
		Craving and chewing ice: A sign of anemia?
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Craving and chewing ice (pagophagia) is often associated with iron deficiency anemia.
	</Abstract>
	<Question>
		Is constantly craving and chewing ice a sign of anemia?
	</Question>
